On your core stance

“I know I’m not above it—but that’s not the point”

Right. The point is:

You don’t need to be above it—you need systems that catch you when you’re inside it.

That’s the difference between:
	•	willpower-based control (fragile)
	•	constraint-based control (durable)

⸻

Final compression (clean, usable)

Use force rarely.
Define exits before entry.
Audit after action.
Never let a tool become your identity.

